First, let‚Äôs pin down what the red‚Äêboxed region is in Figure 2.  That box surrounds the very first step of the whole pipeline: ‚ÄúPrompt Template Design.‚Äù  In other words, whenever RMCBench builds a new task‚Äîwhether it‚Äôs text-to-code or code-to-code‚Äîthe authors start by sketching out a high-level template that says:

